The course supports the compiling of the BA-thesis. The topics relate to the theoretical and methodological principles of writing a BA-thesis; in addition, several practical tips are given for enforcing the writing process and the successful defence of the thesis. An integral part of the course is feedback to students' chapters from their BA-theses and the pre-defence of BA-theses.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course gives students the opportunity to: - get to know the main research methods in the field of language, literature and culture research; - increase their knowledge about the different possibilities of analysis in the respective research branch chosen by them; - develop the ability to independently pose a topical research question, to gather and interpret information; - to complement their practical skills in creating a scientific text and get an overview of the requirements set for a BA thesis.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course, the student:
- has the essential practical skills and a grasp of the theoretical principles necessary for conducting academic research;
- understands the cultural differences between Estonian and Scandinavian academic writing, and takes them into account in their research;
- has a grasp of the methodological principles of composing a scientific text;
- finds necessary information for their research by using appropriate methods, and evaluates the information critically;
- uses relevant digital resources for finding information and formatting their thesis;
- gives the author oral and written feedback on an academic text;
- has a command of academic, field-specific Scandinavian language.
